05/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- In his first press interview since taking office, new Transport and Communications Minister Xhemail Mehazi has vowed to step up efforts to fight corruption. Speaking to the Skopje daily Utrinski Vesnik, Mehazi described corruption as a serious problem in the country, adding that it stems from low wages and delays in reforming the public administration. He also vowed to boost the public image of his ministry, which many view as the most corrupt in the cabinet. (Utrinski Vesnik - 05/01/05) 
